<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-057-035 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 362 135</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 20 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Markets Direct offers automated EDI. (electronic data interchange)(FaxForm software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Markets Direct (Product introduction).andO;Product:   FaxForm (Communications software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionOrder EntryData CommunicationsElectronic data interchangeCommunications software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MARKETS DIRECT OFFERS AUTOMATED EDI 09/20/91 COLORADO SPRINGS, COLORADO,U.S.A., 1991 SEP 20 (NB) -- Markets Direct, a new company, wants to combinePCs, EDI standards, and satellite transmission into a complete system formoving product orders worldwide.andP;  The company has targeted the mail-ordermarket.andM;Here's how it works.andP;  Customers use Markets Direct's new FaxForm 1.0software, an order entry product, to create a purchase order.andP;  This assuresthat the electronic purchase orders look just like their paper cousins.andP;  Thesoftware then transmits the purchase order by fax to Markets Direct'scomputer, which transmits it by satellite to member firms in a formatcompatible with the members' order entry procedures.andP;  The result is a form ofprotocol translation.andP;  The hang-up, of course, is that in order to get orreceive orders, you must be part of Market Directs' network.andM;The company is divided into three divisions: sales and software development,sales of computer and satellite reception hardware, and satellitebroadcasting.andP;  The company admits that its industry is in its infancy, butsays that large companies like Levi Straus, Hallmark, IBM, and Sears havealready experimented with the concept.andP;  &quot;The only impediment to open trade&quot;among the U.S., Europe and the Pacific Rim, &quot;is the lack of a distinctelectronic system to orderly manage the trade transactions of the worldwidemarketplace,&quot; the company concludes in a press release.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910919/Press Contact: Bob Coyne, Markets Direct,800-748-1895; 719-591-8630)</TEXT></DOC>